reviews.text: La Carreta has great food. They can almost always seat you immediately. Their chips and salsa are on point. Their decor is very traditional. The restaurant is clean as well as the restrooms. They have a lot of choices on the menu. There is a separate bar area which serves food later in the evening. It's a family oriented restaurant as well. It's even a fun place to wear a sombrero and be sung to on your birthday! Definitely recommended.

We like Mexican food and we found the second one we like after our previous one closed. It probably deserves 5 stars but only having been there once now it didn't seem appropriate to give more than 4. But don't let that stop you! The food is excellent, service friendly and professional and the place is very clean. They have tables and booths, a full bar, orders to go and party trays and appetizers. Their menu includes; Lunch Menu, specials, Dinner Combos, Fajitas & More lists. They also have a full bar and a wine and beer list. They are Locally Owned & Operated and have been in Gresham for 27 years. We will definitely be going back!

Easily the best Mexican food you can get in Gresham. Some of the most consistently best customer service I have recieved by a restaurant. Every trip is always a great experience, leaving me satisfied by the end of the meal. Our family holds a lot of our celebrations at their establishment and are never disappointed. Food is excellent and drinks are never skimped on. Highly recommended to anyone wanting good food, good drinks, and good service.
Been a favorite for over 20 plus years! Everything is always great from the food to the service! Always fun to go on the weekends when they have music!
Excellent food, good service.  Large servings so there was enough to take home for tomorrow's lunch. And Raul is a kind and gracious server. I highly recommend him. Gracias, Raul.
Everything we had was really excellent;  these people really care about food and hospitality.
Small but very friendly with great food
Always very, very, very good. Exceptional service, exceptional food, fantastic setting. Need I say more? Have you reserved a table yet?
Great food. A little cramped inside but lovely outside on the street if weather permits.
Great italian place. Food is awesome and italian wines.

Crab cake and seasonal dry aged rib eye steak are made to perfection. However the porterhouse steak was not as amazing in comparison. If you are looking for juicy, strong flavour of beef and tender meat, dry aged rib eye is definitely the wise choice. Overall portion is quite big, especially for the sides.
Never disappointing. Personable staff remember my name. Food prepared to perfection. Monthly special menus keep things interesting with excellent seasonal offerings.

I love the sliders at this place! It's perfect as a quick snack. The bun is so fresh and delicious and the meat is cooked to perfection! 

The service is professional and welcoming.

Morton's has grown to over 74 restaurants, but the vision is the same today as it was when we opened our first restaurant in Chicago in 1978. Quality. Consistency. Genuine Hospitality. Prime Beef at Morton's is aged for 23-28 days is so  delicious.
crab cake  is also a yummy dish.
Probably the best steakhouse in town! Well choices of steak cut and cooked very well! Food other than steak is a bit salty though
